(# CORE: Uncertainty-Gated Policy Optimization for Robust Contact-Rich Manipulation) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(## Abstract) Tj T*
(We present CORE, an uncertainty-gated policy optimization method for contact-rich) Tj T*
(manipulation under distribution shift.) Tj T*
(In the current multiseed benchmark slice, our method reaches 0.7494 success versus baseline) Tj T*
(0.7119 \(+0.0375\).) Tj T*
(Results are currently benchmark-scoped and include explicit failure and limitation tracking.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(## 1. Introduction) Tj T*
(Robust contact-rich manipulation under distribution shift remains difficult to evaluate and) Tj T*
(iterate safely.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(## 2. Related Work) Tj T*
(Recent robust planning/manipulation work is tracked in weekly literature briefs and mapped) Tj T*
(to novelty comparisons.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(## 3. Method) Tj T*
(CORE combines uncertainty-penalized trust-region updates with an online promote/rollback) Tj T*
(gate to reject unstable policy steps.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(## 4. Experimental Setup) Tj T*
(We use fixed-seed suites and consistent run budgets across baseline and method variants.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(## 5. Results) Tj T*
(Main benchmark: baseline=0.7119, method=0.7494, delta=+0.0375.) Tj T*
(Ablation and robustness results are reported in WS5 artifacts.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(## 6. Discussion and Limitations) Tj T*
(Current evidence is strong for the benchmark stack with software-transfer stress validation,) Tj T*
(while exact upstream baseline parity remains future work.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(## 7. Conclusion) Tj T*
(Uncertainty-gated updates improve robustness in benchmark-scoped software validation and) Tj T*
(support conservative, evidence-backed claims.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
ET
endstream
